SIMPLE: previous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Previous
<hw>Pre"vi*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praevius</ets> going before, leading the way; <ets>prae</ets>
before + <ets>via</ets> the way. See <er>Voyage</er>.]</ety> <def>Going
before in time; being or happening before something else; antecedent;
prior; <as>as, <ex>previous</ex> arrangements; a <ex>previous</ex>
illness.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The dull sound . . . <qex>previous</qex> to the storm,⟦br⟧
Rolls o'er the muttering earth.</q> <rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Previous question</b></col>. <fld>(Parliamentary
Practice)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Question</er>, and compare
<er>Closure</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Previous to</b></col>, <cd>before; --
often used adverbially for <xex>previously</xex>.</cd>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Previous to</xex> publication.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>M. Arnold.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧A policy . . . his friends had advised <xex>previous to</xex>
1710.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>J. H. Newman.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Antecedent; preceding; anterior; prior;
foregoing; former.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Previously</ent>⟦br⟧
